<subSubSection id="C3776556EEDE3BA7FCEFF907FD1EFDDA" lastPageId="402" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="399" pageNumber="400" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEDE3BA7FCEFF907FD1EFDDA" blockId="399.[810,1452,1737,2071]" lastBlockId="402.[136,778,173,1832]" lastPageId="402" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="399" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEDE3BBAFCEFF907FC58F922" bold="true" box="[810,925,1737,1763]" pageId="399" pageNumber="400">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body of female consisting of swollen prosome and narrow, cylindrical urosome. Cephalosomewelldefinedbydorsalcephalic shield.Metasome unsegmented, strongly inflated, forming brood pouch incorporatingfifth pedigeroussomite. Freeurosome 5-segmented. Caudal ramus armed with 4 spines + 2 setae, or 3 spines + 3 setae. Rostrum present. Antennule 8- to 10-segmented. Antenna uniramous and 4-segmented, composed of coxa, basis and 2-segmented endopod. Mandible as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEDE3BBAFAEDF814FA66F832" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1859" box="[1320,1443,2010,2035]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="399" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEDE3BBAFAEDF814FA66F832" box="[1320,1443,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="399" pageNumber="400">Doropygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; exopod with 5 setae (distalmost seta may be vestigial); endopod with 4 setae on first segment and 8 or 9 setae on second. Maxillule armedwith 3 setae on basis, 4 setae on exopod and 2 on endopod. Maxilla lacking claw on basis; endopod 3-segmented with 3 or 4 setae on terminal segment. Maxilliped indistinctly 2-segmented, armed with 9 setae on first segment and 2 setae on second. Leg 1 with 3-segmented rami; basis with inner distal spine. Legs 2–4 each with 3-segmented exopod and 2- or 3-segmented endopod. Third exopodal segment of leg 4 armed with only 8 armature elements. Leg 5 consistingof protopod and free exopodal segment bearing 2 distal elements.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF126655EEC13BA5FF4DF8BDFDD3F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591815" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4591815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591815/files/figure.png" pageId="400" pageNumber="401" startId="400.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[246,1337,212,1861]" targetPageId="400">
