</taxonomicNameLabel>
is superficially similarto 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FF36FCB9FEB6FC50" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[243,371,887,913]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Bonnierilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FF36FCB9FEB6FC50" box="[243,371,887,913]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Bonnierilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhavingthebroodpouchof theadult female consisting of the entire unsegmented metasome (comprising pedigeroussomites 1 to 4). However, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FED0FC13FE50FC36" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[277,405,989,1015]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Bonnierilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FED0FC13FE50FC36" box="[277,405,989,1015]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Bonnierilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it is characterised by the endopod of the maxilluleusually being armed with 4 setae, the 2-segmented condition of the maxilliped which has an elongate second segment, legs 1 and 2 usually lack the inner coxal seta, the elongate exopods of the swimming legs, and the enlarged outer seta on the basis of leg 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEC33BA7FF78FB67FD9FF9D9" blockId="402.[136,778,173,1832]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FF78FB67FEFEFB02" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,315,1193,1219]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Chelipygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FF78FB67FEFEFB02" box="[189,315,1193,1219]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Chelipygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEC33BA7FE83FB67FE70FB05" box="[326,437,1193,1220]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FE83FB67FE6BFB02" bold="true" box="[326,430,1193,1219]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similarto 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FD93FB64FD0BFB02" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[598,718,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Notopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FD93FB64FD0BFB02" box="[598,718,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Notopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEC33BA7FD1CFB67FF7EFB27" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FD1CFB67FF71FB24" bold="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having an inflated prosome and spines on the caudal rami, but can be separated from the latter genus by the possession of 5 setae (or 4 setae plus a vestigial seta) on the mandibular exopod, less than 10 setae on the mandibular endopod, 4 and 2 setae on the exopod and endopod, respectively, of themaxillule (instead of 3 setae on both rami as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FE91FA56FE09FA70" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[340,460,1432,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Notopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FE91FA56FE09FA70" box="[340,460,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Notopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEC33BA7FE17FA56FDFCFA73" box="[466,569,1432,1458]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FE17FA56FDF0FA73" bold="true" box="[466,565,1432,1458]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), no differentiated claw on the basis of the maxilla, and a total of 8 armature elements on the third exopodal segment of leg 4 (instead of 9 elements as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FEA4FA30FE1CF9D6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[353,473,1534,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Notopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FEA4FA30FE1CF9D6" box="[353,473,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Notopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEC33BA7FE25FA30FD8DF9D9" box="[480,584,1534,1560]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FE25FA30FD81F9D9" bold="true" box="[480,580,1534,1560]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEC33BA7FF78F9EEFD14F8E9" blockId="402.[136,778,173,1832]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FF78F9EEFE3CF9FB" authority="Illg, 1970" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1970" box="[189,505,1567,1594]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalai">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FF78F9EEFE4EF9F8" box="[189,395,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Doropygus catalai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEEC33BA7FE4AF9D1FE3CF9FB" author="Illg" box="[399,505,1567,1594]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" pagination="169 - 188" part="18" refId="ref328965" refString="Illg, P. L. (1970 a) Report on ascidicole Copepoda collected during the Melanesia Expedition of the Osaka Museum of Natural History, Osaka, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 18, 169 - 188." title="Report on ascidicole Copepoda collected during the Melanesia Expedition of the Osaka Museum of Natural History, Osaka, Japan" type="journal article" year="1970">Illg, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
wasoriginallydescribed as an associate of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FE97F98FFCCFF99D" authority="(Oka, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="Oka" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[338,778,1601,1628]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Ascidiidae" genus="Ascidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="sydneiensis" subSpecies="samea">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FE97F98FFDB9F99A" box="[338,636,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Ascidia sydneiensis samea</emphasis>
(Oka, 1935)
</taxonomicName>
sampled in 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DEEC33BA7FEDFF9AAFE15F9BC" box="[282,464,1635,1662]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEEC33BA7FE2DF9ADFDA7F9BF" author="Illg" box="[488,610,1635,1662]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" pagination="169 - 188" part="18" refId="ref328965" refString="Illg, P. L. (1970 a) Report on ascidicole Copepoda collected during the Melanesia Expedition of the Osaka Museum of Natural History, Osaka, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 18, 169 - 188." title="Report on ascidicole Copepoda collected during the Melanesia Expedition of the Osaka Museum of Natural History, Osaka, Japan" type="journal article" year="1970">Illg, 1970</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEEC33BA7FDBBF9ADFCCFF9BF" author="Kim, I. - H." bookContentInfo="138 pp." box="[638,778,1635,1662]" journalOrPublisher="National Institute of Biological Resources, Ministry of Environment, Korea" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" refId="ref329328" refString="Kim, I. - H. (2012) Invertebrate fauna of Korea, vol. 21, no. 20. Ascidicolous Copepods. Flora and Fauna of Korea. National Institute of Biological Resources, Ministry of Environment, Korea, 138 pp." title="Invertebrate fauna of Korea, vol. 21, no. 20. Ascidicolous Copepods. Flora and Fauna of Korea" type="book" year="2012">Kim (2012)</bibRefCitation>
rediscovered this species in 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DEEC33BA7FE08F948FDD4F961" box="[461,529,1670,1696]" name="South Korea" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Korea</collectingCountry>
and observed that its caudal rami carry 3 spines and 3 setae, and it shares the other character states of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FE60F907FDE6F922" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[421,547,1737,1763]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Chelipygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FE60F907FDE6F922" box="[421,547,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Chelipygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEC33BA7FDE8F904FD5FF925" box="[557,666,1738,1764]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FDE8F904FD51F925" bold="true" box="[557,660,1738,1764]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, as listed in the generic diagnosis. It is here transferred to the new genus as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEC33BA7FF2AF8C3FD8DF8E6" authority="(Illg, 1970)" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Illg" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[239,584,1805,1832]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Chelipygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalai" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FF2AF8C3FE07F8E6" box="[239,450,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">Chelipygus catalai</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEEC33BA7FE14F8C3FDFAF8E9" author="Illg" box="[465,575,1805,1832]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" pagination="169 - 188" part="18" refId="ref328965" refString="Illg, P. L. (1970 a) Report on ascidicole Copepoda collected during the Melanesia Expedition of the Osaka Museum of Natural History, Osaka, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 18, 169 - 188." title="Report on ascidicole Copepoda collected during the Melanesia Expedition of the Osaka Museum of Natural History, Osaka, Japan" type="journal article" year="1970">Illg, 1970</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FDFAF8C3FD8DF8E6" bold="true" box="[575,584,1805,1831]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEC33BA7FD8AF8C0FD14F8E9" box="[591,721,1806,1832]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEC33BA7FD8AF8C0FD0FF8E9" bold="true" box="[591,714,1806,1832]" pageId="402" pageNumber="403">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
